rComments: Just an awful prof. Tax is a course which needs some guidance and filtering of materials because there is so much nuanced information, and is absolutely no help in doing that. His lectures are useless he just reads off the textbooks lecture notes in barely undersrandable tone.

I’m taking online course with him now and its the most stupid thing I ever made in my school life. Tests are impossible, final will be harder, no time to complete long questions. This guy assigns 60% to the final, but someone told me the other pro assigns 50% to the final. Same school, different pro, different marking system, go figure…

He spoke English but it sounded like he spoke in another language. I could hardly understand the words came out of his mouth. Powerpoint notes are long with a lot of pointless notes. If you can’t teach yourself, you’re screwed.
The worst pro ever in my school life. I heard bad reviews about him, but I gave him the benefit of the doubt, and I made a biggest mistake. If you find an alternative, take it.
James is a good instructor. He is very helpful. Like all course you will have to study on your own as well. Not everything can be covered in a 3 hour class. He is an easy marker.
Personally I don't like the way he teaches and don't find it helpful at all. He is not clear with his lectures, confuses himself and in turn, students suffer. AVOID HIM AT ALL COSTS!
I dropped the course. I couldn't stand the way he was mumbling with the words. He shown no interest with the topic. Very boring man.
